			"description": "<ul>\n<li>You have blindsight with a range of 90 feet.</li>\n<li>You have advantage on saving throws to disbelieve illusions.</li>\n<li>You have advantage on Perception checks to locate invisible creatures.</li>\n<li>Making ranged weapon attacks at long range does not impose disadvantage on you (you must still abide by a weapon’s maximum range). </li>\n<li>You can also ignore half and three-quarters cover when making ranged attacks. </li>\n<li>Non-solid, particulate obstacles like smoke and fog that would normally heavily obscure an area only lightly obscure it for you.</li>\n<li>You have Truesight with a range of 60 feet.</li>\n</ul>",
